Privacy Policy
Last updated: 03 February 2026
This Privacy Policy describes how Cards Local (“the App”) handles user data.
Information We Collect
The App does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data to external servers.
The App accesses and stores local data on the user’s device (such as game settings and game progress) only to ensure proper functionality of the App.
Without access to local data, the App cannot function correctly.
Tracking
The App does not use tracking technologies and does not track users across apps or websites.
Third-Party Services
The App does not use third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs.
Data Storage
All data is stored locally on the user’s device only.
No data is uploaded or shared.
Internet Connectivity
The App can function offline.
No personal data is sent to external servers.
Children’s Privacy
The App does not knowingly collect any personal information from children.
Changes to This Policy
If this policy changes, the updated version will be made available at this URL.
Contact
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, contact:
pitbiren@gmail.com


